    <briefdescription>
<para>IEEE 802.15.4 L2 APIs. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="since"><para>1.0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="version"><para>0.8.0</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
<para>This API provides integration with Zephyr&apos;s sockets and network contexts. <bold>Application and driver developers should never interface directly with this API.</bold> It is of interest to subsystem maintainers only.</para>
<para>The API implements and extends the following structures:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>implements Zephyr&apos;s internal L2-level socket and network context abstractions (context/socket operations, see <ref refid="group__net__l2" kindref="compound">Network L2 Abstraction Layer</ref>),</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>protocol-specific extension to the interface structure (see <ref refid="group__net__if" kindref="compound">Network Interface abstraction layer</ref>)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>protocol-specific extensions to the network packet structure (see <ref refid="group__net__pkt" kindref="compound">Network Packet Library</ref>),</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>All section, table and figure references are to the IEEE 802.15.4-2020 standard. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
